{"id": "EUVD-2018-8672", "enisaUuid": "50bcbddb-75bc-3b4a-8752-6b6219445fd2", "description": "A use-after-free issue was found in the way the Linux kernel's KVM hypervisor processed posted interrupts when nested(=1) virtualization is enabled. In nested_get_vmcs12_pages(), in case of an error while processing posted interrupt address, it unmaps the 'pi_desc_page' without resetting 'pi_desc' descriptor address, which is later used in pi_test_and_clear_on(). A guest user/process could use this flaw to crash the host kernel resulting in DoS or potentially gain privileged access to a system. Kernel versions before 4.14.91 and before 4.19.13 are vulnerable.", "datePublished": "2019-01-03T16:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T10:32:54", "baseScore": 6.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:C/C:N/I:L/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-16882.html", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-16882", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2018-16882.html", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2018-16882.html", "https://marc.info/?l=kvm&m=154514994222809&w=2", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3872-1/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3878-1/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3871-5/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3878-2/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3871-4/", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/106254", "https://lwn.net/Articles/775720/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3871-1/", "https://lwn.net/Articles/775721/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3871-3/", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2018-16882", "https://support.f5.com/csp/article/K80557033"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-16882"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.11, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1009cb41-f2b6-37cd-858f-a449f07b357b", "product": {"name": "kernel:"}, "product_version": "before 4.14.91"}, {"id": "576387f7-49ac-3868-9536-e718fa3166f7", "product": {"name": "kernel:"}, "product_version": "before 4.19.13"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "08fed7a0-5d4f-35f4-8d5a-c787c43a306f", "vendor": {"name": "The L